# KNIGHTS TEMPLAR v6.0 — PHOTOREALISTIC ART GUIDE

## Overview

This document contains every AI art prompt needed to upgrade the game from procedural SVG to photorealistic scene art. **23 images total** — 17 rooms, 3 enemies, and 3 special scenes.

---

## Technical Specs

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Dimensions** | 1600×560px (2:1 ratio, renders at 800×280 in game) |
| **Format** | .webp (best compression for web) |
| **Max file size** | 150KB each (aim for 80-120KB) |
| **Total budget** | ~2.5MB for all 23 images |
| **Style** | Dark fantasy / Gothic horror, painterly-photorealistic |
| **Lighting** | Dramatic chiaroscuro, single warm light source + cold ambient |
| **Color palette** | Deep blacks, warm golds, blood reds, cold stone blues |
| **Camera** | Wide-angle interior/exterior, slightly low angle (heroic perspective) |

### Consistent Style Suffix (append to ALL prompts)

```
dark medieval gothic horror, dramatic chiaroscuro lighting, photorealistic digital painting, 
ultra detailed stone textures, atmospheric fog, cinematic composition, wide angle, 
aspect ratio 20:7, dark fantasy color palette with deep blacks warm golds and blood reds, 
unreal engine quality, artstation trending, 8k detail
```

---

## FILE STRUCTURE

Place all images in a folder called `img/` next to `game.html`:

```
game.html
img/
  chapel.webp
  cloister.webp
  armory.webp
  scriptorium.webp
  barracks.webp
  infirmary.webp
  bellTower.webp
  courtyard.webp
  cryptEntrance.webp
  catacombs.webp
  necromancerLair.webp
  grandHall.webp
  treasury.webp
  boneThrone.webp
  portraitGallery.webp
  dungeonDepths.webp
  watchtower.webp
  enemy_risen.webp
  enemy_peasant.webp
  enemy_necromancer.webp
  scene_golden.webp
  scene_death.webp
  scene_victory.webp
```

